# swagger-java-client

Swagger Petstore
- API version: 1.0.0
  - Build date: 2019-10-14T09:46:20.743+02:00[Europe/Rome]

This is a fork of Petstore server specification.  You can find out more about Swagger at [http://swagger.io](http://swagger.io). For this sample, you can use the api key `special-key` to test the authorization filters.


*Automatically generated by the [Swagger Codegen](https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-codegen)*


## Requirements

Building the API client library requires:
1. Java 1.7+
2. Maven/Gradle

## Installation

To install the API client library to your local Maven repository, simply execute:

```shell
mvn clean install
```

To deploy it to a remote Maven repository instead, configure the settings of the repository and execute:

```shell
mvn clean deploy
```

Refer to the [OSSRH Guide](http://central.sonatype.org/pages/ossrh-guide.html) for more information.

### Maven users

Add this dependency to your project's POM:

```xml
<dependency>
  <groupId>io.swagger</groupId>
  <artifactId>swagger-java-client</artifactId>
  <version>1.0.0</version>
  <scope>compile</scope>
</dependency>
```

### Gradle users

Add this dependency to your project's build file:

```groovy
compile "io.swagger:swagger-java-client:1.0.0"
```

### Others

At first generate the JAR by executing:

```shell
mvn clean package
```

Then manually install the following JARs:

* `target/swagger-java-client-1.0.0.jar`
* `target/lib/*.jar`

        PetApi apiInstance = new PetApi();
        Pet body = new Pet(); // Pet | Pet object that needs to be added to the store

            Pet result = apiInstance.addPet(body);

        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling PetApi#addPet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Class | Method | HTTP request | Description
------------ | ------------- | ------------- | -------------
*PetApi* | [**addPet**](docs/PetApi.md#addPet) | **POST** /pet | Add a new pet to the store
*PetApi* | [**deletePet**](docs/PetApi.md#deletePet) | **DELETE** /pet/{petId} | Deletes a pet
*PetApi* | [**findPetsByStatus**](docs/PetApi.md#findPetsByStatus) | **GET** /pet/findByStatus | Finds Pets by status
*PetApi* | [**findPetsByTags**](docs/PetApi.md#findPetsByTags) | **GET** /pet/findByTags | Finds Pets by tags
*PetApi* | [**getPetById**](docs/PetApi.md#getPetById) | **GET** /pet/{petId} | Find pet by ID
*PetApi* | [**getPets**](docs/PetApi.md#getPets) | **GET** /pet | Get List of Pets
*PetApi* | [**updatePet**](docs/PetApi.md#updatePet) | **PUT** /pet | Update an existing pet

## Documentation for Authorization

Authentication schemes defined for the API:
### api_key

- **Type**: API key
- **API key parameter name**: api_key
- **Location**: HTTP header

### petstore_auth

- **Type**: OAuth
- **Flow**: implicit
- **Authorization URL**: https://petstore.swagger.io/oauth/authorize
- **Scopes**: 
  - :
